 partner simply takes over the lead. Explain that this shows how easily people can collaborate and share leadership in a project.<br>When finished, discuss, asking guiding questions like:<br><em> How did these variations make mirroring more interesting?<br></em> How did mirroring help you understand your partner’s movements and feelings?<br>Explain that these mirroring skills help us understand others and work together, just like people do when building new things or creating new ideas.<br><strong>Innovation Blueprint Challenge</strong><br>Explain to the class that they will brainstorm ideas for their upcoming final mirroring pieces. Divide students into pairs (or utilize the pre-existing pairs). Provide each student with a piece of paper and writing utensil.<br><em>Sketch an Idea</em><br><em> Instruct each student to quickly draw a very simple “blueprint” or sketch of one new invention or strong structure related to Global Goal 9 (e.g., a super fast train, a giant recycling machine, a new kind of school, a strong bridge, a robot helper, etc.).<br></em>Create a Key Movement<em><br></em> Instruct each student to think about their drawing and create one key movement or gesture that captures the essence of their invention or structure (e.g., a swift smooth gesture for the train, a strong steady pose for the bridge, a repeating whirring movement for the recycling machine).<br><em>Mirror the Blueprint</em><br><em> Instruct pairs to share their drawings with their partner. Then, one partner performs their key movement, while the other partner mirrors it. Repeat for the second partner’s idea.<br></em>Discuss and Choose<em><br></em> After mirroring, each pair discusses which of their ideas (or a combination) they want to focus on for their collaborative mirroring piece.<br>Circulate, offering guidance and asking guiding questions like:<br><em> How does your movement show the strength of your bridge?<br></em> Can you partner clearly mirror your robot helper gesture?<br><em> Which idea makes the best movement story for mirroring?<br><strong>Mirroring Innovation: Creating Movement Pieces</strong><br>Explain that each pair will now create a short (45-60 second) mirroring movement piece that tells a story about Industry, Innovation, or Infrastructure from Global Goal 9, using the skills practiced and the brainstormed ideas.<br>Instruct pairs to choose a central idea for their piece (e.g., building a strong bridge, a new invention being created, people working together fairly).<br>Encourage pairs to include:<br></em> <em>Clear Leader/Follower:</em> Start with a clear leader, then maybe switch roles smoothly in hte middle.<br><em> </em>Dynamic Changes:<em> Go from slow to fast, soft to strong, or use different levels to show parts of the story.<br></em> <em>Symbolic Movements:</em> Use movements from the brainstorm (or new ones) that represent building, inventing, growth, or solving a problem.<br><em> </em>The Power of Connection:<em> Show how the mirroring itself emphasizes teamwork and understanding.<br>Play varied music during creation time that is upbeat and empowering. Music examples:<br></em> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V3jjH-_LVG4&amp;list=PLrgkRQ9954-Rv7gNesYeAzmjwzuBbkM47&amp;index=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Hip Hop Instrumentals Playlist</a><br><em> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RIu4vp_PuXU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Upbeat Instrumental Music</a> Playlist<br></em> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gs-aqFcAOQk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Cheerful Instrumental Bops</a> Playlist<br>Circulate, offering guidance and asking guiding questions like:<br><em> How can your mirroring show the strength of a new building?<br></em> Can you have one partner show a problem and the other mirror a solution?<br><em> Are you listening and responding to each other’s movements?<br><strong>Reflection and Summary</strong><br>Have students reflect on their learning experience through discussion or writing.<br>Ask guiding questions like:<br></em> How did the practice of mirroring (reflecting another person’s movements) help you understand the concept of collaboration and interconnectedness that is central to Global Goal 9?<br><em> What did you learn about non-verbal communication and empathy through mirroring? How might these skills be important in building global partnerships for innovation and infrastructure?<br></em> What new insights did you gain about Global Goal 9 and the importance of industry, innovation, and infrastructure through the movement exploration?<br><em> What role do you think shared understanding and aligned actions (like in mirroring) play in achieving sustainable industrialization or resilient infrastructure?<br></em> Hoe did connecting to abstract concepts (like innovation or infrastructure) help you to see the human element within the goals of industry, innovation, and infrastructure?<br><em> What are some ways that you can continue to use movement, dance, or collaborative thinking to raise awareness or advocate for Global Goal 9 in your daily life?<br><strong>Assessment</strong><br></em> Consistent and enthusiastic involvement in all phases of the lesson, including the warm up, mirroring exercises, creative movement, and class discussions.<br><em> Understanding of the core concept of industry, innovation, and infrastructure (building, new ideas, fair industry), as demonstrated through the symbolism and intention within the movement pieces and verbal explanations during sharing and discussion.<br></em> Originality and effectiveness in using mirroring techniques (e.g., precise reflection, leading/following variations, incorporating levels/qualities) to convey the chosen message about industry, innovation, and/or infrastructure. Look for clear expression of ideas through the movement.<br><em> Ability to work effectively with partners, demonstrating active listening, responsiveness, and mutual support during the mirroring and creative movement phases.<br></em> Ability to articulate learning and personal connections during the reflection and summary discussion."} {sdgColor} />

